content.title: Simple Calculator
content.description:
Create a simple calculator that performs basic arithmetic operations on two integers.

**Problem Description:**
You are given an array containing two integers `a` and `b`, and a mathematical operator `c`. Your task is to implement a function that performs the specified operation and returns the result.

**Input Format:**
- An array `[a, b]` where `a` and `b` are integers
- A character `c` representing the mathematical operator

**Output Format:**
- Return the result of the calculation as an integer
- For division operations, return only the integer part (truncate towards zero)
- Return `-1` if the operation cannot be performed (e.g., division by zero)

**Constraints:**
- `-100 <= a, b <= 100`
- `c` is one of: `'+'`, `'-'`, `'*'`, `'/'`

**Examples:**

Example 1:
```
Input: [1, 3], '+'
Output: 4
Explanation: 1 + 3 = 4
```

Example 2:
```
Input: [1, 0], '/'
Output: -1
Explanation: Division by zero is not allowed, return -1
```

Example 3:
```
Input: [7, 3], '/'
Output: 2
Explanation: 7 / 3 = 2.33..., return integer part: 2
```

**Function Signature:**
```java
public int calculate(int[] nums, char operator)
```

**Note:** This problem tests your understanding of basic arithmetic operations, input validation, and error handling.

content.title: Trapping Rain Water
content.description: Given n non-negative integers representing an elevation map where the width of each bar is 1, compute how much water it can trap after raining.

content.title: Longest Valid Parentheses
content.description: Given a string containing just the characters '(' and ')', find the length of the longest valid (well-formed) parentheses substring.

content.title: Merge k Sorted Lists
content.description: You are given an array of k linked-lists lists, each linked-list is sorted in ascending order. Merge all the linked-lists into one sorted linked-list and return it.

content.title: Regular Expression Matching
content.description: Given an input string s and a pattern p, implement regular expression matching with support for '.' and '*' where: '.' Matches any single character. '*' Matches zero or more of the preceding element.

content.title: Median of Two Sorted Arrays
content.description: Given two sorted arrays nums1 and nums2 of size m and n respectively, return the median of the two sorted arrays.

content.title: Product of Array Except Self
content.description: Given an integer array nums, return an array answer such that answer[i] is equal to the product of all the elements of nums except nums[i].

content.title: Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters
content.description: Given a string s, find the length of the longest substring without repeating characters.

content.title: 3Sum
content.description: Given an integer array nums, return all the triplets [nums[i], nums[j], nums[k]] such that i != j, i != k, and j != k, and nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k] == 0.

content.title: Container With Most Water
content.description: You are given an integer array height of length n. There are n vertical lines drawn such that the two endpoints of the ith line are (i, 0) and (i, height[i]). Find two lines that together with the x-axis form a container, such that the container contains the most water.

content.title: Longest Palindromic Substring
content.description: Given a string s, return the longest palindromic substring in s.

content.title: Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock
content.description: You are given an array prices where prices[i] is the price of a given stock on the ith day. You want to maximize your profit by choosing a single day to buy one stock and choosing a different day in the future to sell that stock.

content.title: Climbing Stairs
content.description: You are climbing a staircase. It takes n steps to reach the top. Each time you can either climb 1 or 2 steps. In how many distinct ways can you climb to the top?

content.title: Maximum Subarray
content.description: Given an integer array nums, find the contiguous subarray (containing at least one number) which has the largest sum and return its sum.

content.title: Valid Parentheses
content.description: Given a string s containing just the characters '(', ')', '{', '}', '[' and ']', determine if the input string is valid.

content.title: Two Sum
content.description: Given an array of integers nums and an integer target, return indices of the two numbers such that they add up to target.
